section
  h2 Search engines
  p Search websites according to:
  ul
    li Robots.txt
    li Sitemap.xml

section
  h2 Robots.txt
  p First landing page for a web crawler
  pre
    code.
      Sitemap: http://myhost.com/sitemap.xml
      User-agent: *
      Disallow: /secure/
      Disallow: /tmp/

section
  h2 Security considerations
  p.read-block robots <b>can ignore your /robots.txt</b>, especially malware robots.
  p.read-block <b>Anyone can see</b> which sections of your server are secured.

section
  h2 Sitemap.xml
  p Inform search engines <b>about pages available for crawling</b>
  pre
    code.
      #{'<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>'}
      #{'<urlset xmlns="http://www.sitemaps.org/schemas/sitemap/0.9">'}
         #{'<url>'}
            #{'<loc>http://www.example.com/index.html</loc>'}
            #{'<lastmod>2005-01-01</lastmod>'}
            #{'<changefreq>daily</changefreq>'}
            #{'<priority>0.8</priority>'}
         #{'</url>'}
      #{'</urlset>'}

section
  h2 Contents missing in the sitemap
  p <b>Will be indexed as well</b> if they get linked somewhere

section
  h2 So why use sitemaps?
  ul.read-block
    li Specify <b>frequency of change</b> and <b>priorities</b>
    li Point to <b>otherwise unreachable contents</b>.

