section
  h2 PageRank
  p Algorithm by Larry Page (Google) used to measure the weight of a page in the Internet

section
  h2 Bits included in PageRank
  ul.read-block
    li <b>Page URL</b> and <b>host name</b>
    li <b>Title</b> and <b>description</b> of the page
    li Website <b>performance</b>
    li <b>Language</b> deduced by the search engine
    li <b>Contents</b> structure
    li <b>Referrals</b>

section
  h2 Bits NOT included in PageRank
  ul.read-block
    li #{'<meta '}<b>name=keywords></b>
    li <b>Language</b> set in the page
    li <b>Invisible contents</b>
    li #{'<a rel="'}<b>nofollow</b>">

section
  h2 Clean URLs
  p Use hyphens to separate words, not underscores
  p /posts/why_seo_rocks  <b>WRONG</b>
  p /posts/why-seo-rocks  <b>CORRECT</b>

section
  h2 Meta robots
  ul.read-block
    li <b>nofollow</b>: do not follow any link on this page.
    li <b>noindex</b>: do not store this page in the search engine index. 
    li <b>noarchive</b>: do not store a cached version of the page.
    li There is also <b>follow, index</b>, but they are the default behavior.
  a.source(href="https://developers.google.com/webmasters/control-crawl-index/docs/robots_meta_tag") Source: Google for Webmasters

